<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-18T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="654" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d654">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17894</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                all <gloss type="to">American Consuls in Mexico except those at
                                    Chihuahua City and Mexico City</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-18T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Following for your information and guidance:</p>
                        <p>Letcher reported, 17th: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Colonel Brown telegraphed yesterday from Santa Cruz that
                                    municipal president, Parral, had delivered to him an ultimatum
                                    in writing from commander here, forbidding his troops to advance
                                    one foot more without orders from him or Secretary of War.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Rodgers has been instructed to make representations to the end that local
                            commanders be restrained from independent action.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>